<item>
            <title>[LU-11796] Remove LASSERT(r0-&gt;lo_nr &lt;= lov_targets_nr(dev)) in maintenance branches</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11796</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In reviewing the overstriping patch, Andreas noted that one assert it&apos;s removing should also be removed in the maintenance branches:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/28425/15/lustre/lov/lov_object.c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/28425/15/lustre/lov/lov_object.c&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is because the client is asserting on network data from the server, and the assert is enforcing an expected constraint (num stripes &amp;lt;= num osts), but nothing goes wrong if it&apos;s removed.&#160; In fact, it might be possible for the two to disagree if OSTs go offline.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
